land-based ice melt.

01:01:03.570 --> 01:01:04.580
Not sea ice.

01:01:04.580 --> 01:01:06.530
Sea ice is like ice
cubes in your iced tea.

01:01:06.530 --> 01:01:08.750
When it melts, your iced
tea doesn't overflow.

01:01:08.750 --> 01:01:11.630
But when the ice sheet
melts, it does fill up.

01:01:11.630 --> 01:01:15.050
So you're adding water to the
ocean from glaciers and ice

01:01:15.050 --> 01:01:15.870
sheets.

01:01:15.870 --> 01:01:17.900
So the sea ice melt
doesn't change it,

01:01:17.900 --> 01:01:20.320
but the ice sheet
melt, the shelf melting

01:01:20.320 --> 01:01:22.120
and ice sheet melting does.

01:01:22.120 --> 01:01:24.360
Those are two big factors.

01:01:24.360 --> 01:01:26.630
The third big factor in
